.TH CBT-RUN-SEQ "1" "February 2026" "cbt-run-seq (cbt) 0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cbt-run-seq \- run a sequence
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cbt-run-seq
[\fIOPTION\fR] \fISEQUENCE\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Executes all scripts in a sequence that have been marked as enabled.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-o\fR, \fB\-\-output\-format\fR
Specifies the way the output is presented. 'terminal'
uses the first terminal (/dev/tty1) for displaying the
steps to be executed and the second terminal
(/dev/tty2) for displaying the build progress. 'text'
redirects all output to the standard output and error.
The default is: terminal, unless the DISPLAY
environment variable is set. Then it will be 'text'
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display help page
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Display version
